The people who are serving will be on the trail of those who will not remove the deities of their dog or throw on the ground the cigarette butts, packing materials or cans, but also a sling and dirty urban furnishings such as benches or ludic tools in public parks. As explained by the deputy mayor and advisor to the environment of Merano, Katharina Zeller, "in the first phase the main objective will not be to elevate contraventions but to raise citizens to the issue of cleanliness and decoration of public spaces" specifying that the 'WasteWatcher will also have the faculty to ascertain violations, to identify offenders and to report them to the local police". &nbsp;>

